President Barack Obama has announced the members of the bipartisan National Commission on Fiscal Responsibility and Reform. The commission will be co-chaired by former White House Chief of Staff Erskine Bowles and former Republican Senate Whip Alan Simpson. The members appointed by President Obama include David Cote, chairman and CEO of Honeywell; Ann Fudge, former chairman and CEO of Young & Rubicam Brands; Alice Rivlin, senior fellow at the Brookings Institution; and Andy Stern, president of the Service Employees International Union. The commission will make recommendations to Congress by December 1, 2010, with the goal of achieving a balanced budget by 2015 and improving the long-term fiscal outlook.